Fragrant rice forms the base of this Asian-inspired beef dish. Lemongrass—another aromatic ingredient—is the shining flavour, while vibrant veg adds a satisfying crunch as well as all-important nutrients.

Pour @cold salted water{300%ml} (double for 4p) into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Lower the heat to medium, cover with the lid and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the pot from the heat.

Keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, quarter the @Lime{1}.

Roughly chop the @Coriander{5%g} (stalks and all).

Trim the @Carrot{1} and halve widthways. Chop lengthways into ½ cm thick batons.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Onion{1}.

Place a pan over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the @Irish Beef Strips{250%g} and @Garlic, Ginger & Lemongrass Paste{1%sachet} until the beef is browned, shifting as it colours, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging. Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Remove from the pan and set aside. Cover to keep warm.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the carrot and fry for ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @Broccolini{75%g} and onion to the pan.

Fry for another ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @Vegetable Stock{1%sachet} to the pan along with @water{25%ml}(double for 4p).

Cover and cook until the veg is tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove the pan from the heat.

Stir through the beef strips, @Soy Sauce{1%sachet}, @Sweet Chilli Sauce{1%sachet} and juice from half the lime wedges.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between plates.

Serve the flavourful beef and veg alongside.

Garnish with chopped coriander and remaining lime wedges.

> Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} as needed during cooking.